# OrcOutFit Workflow Rules

- Always update `.claude/work.md` after each notable code change, fix, build, or behavior change before final user reply.
- Never run `git push` unless the user explicitly asks for it.
- After substantial edits, run a verification build for `Release|Win32`.
- Keep runtime logic and docs in sync: update `context.md`, `README.md`, `README.txt` when user asks to finalize.
- For model/skin resolution logic, prioritize model names; use `id###/###` only as fallback.
- Never auto-copy or move `.asi` to game folders; the only valid artifact location is `build\Release\OrcOutFit.asi`.
